messages.message: hey team, i have a pr here (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/71845/files#diff-4a4a476708b8420161cb3a9b53f1609182afcbf3bdedf163204381f51ad353f2) that's failing from cypress tests, and i'm looking at the relevant ones (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/20670/overview/a32f3964-871d-4a5a-a3be-48c688aa5990?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1) (ground-truth-crud.spec.ts), and it's failing i think because backend changes in the same pr haven't been applied, is this expected?

Yep, that’s expected. The Cypress tests currently use the PR’s frontend code. The backend code is not deployed, it’ll always use what’s on `crafting-cyp` cluster.

We do plan to deploy backend code in our Crafting PR sandboxes eventually, when we get time hah.

For now, you can run the test against your local sandbox and confirm it’s working.

Also, when you merge in that PR into master, please trigger a re-deployment in the crafting-cyp (https://sandbox.console.instabase.com/customer/Engineering/tenant/crafting-cyp/info) so that the backend is updated. This will prevent other PRs from being blocked waiting for a redeployment.
